The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Sex-test scan on clinics

 New Delhi, Aug. 11: A national surveillance cell made up of former police officers and non-government organisations will conduct surprise inspections of ultrasound clinics to ensure they are not revealing the sex of foetuses, the health minister has said.

 Dr Punit Bedi, a consultant at Apollo Hospital has estimated that about 25,000 female foetuses had been aborted in the capital over the past year. 




